    {
      "_id": "66f68e2a863375af",
      "name": "Determining if an Attack Hits",
      "ownership": {
        "default": -1
      },
      "sort": 8,
      "text": {
        "content": "<p id=\"1cf1b90a-e081-817a-8285-fab23418aec2\">When a creature makes an Attack, the result of the Attack Check or Spell Check is compared to the target’s Defense to determine whether or not the Attack Hits the target. The Attack Hits if the result of the Attack Check is equal to or greater than the target’s Defense.</p><p id=\"1cf1b90a-e081-81df-8f55-d45548892d3e\" class=\"block-color-blue_background\"><strong>Example: </strong>A Level 4 Champion’s highest Attribute is a <strong>3</strong> (Prime Modifier) and their Combat Mastery is <strong>2</strong> (1/2 its level). When the Champion makes an Attack Check using a Longsword, they roll a d20 and add <strong>5</strong> (2+3). If they roll a 10 on the d20, the result is 15 (10 + 5). If the target’s Physical Defense is 15 or lower, the Attack Hits, otherwise it Misses.</p>",
        "format": 1
      },
      "title": {
        "level": 2,
        "show": true
      },
      "type": "text",
      "system": {},
      "image": {},
      "video": {
        "controls": true,
        "volume": 0.5
      },
      "src": null,
      "flags": {},
      "_stats": {
        "compendiumSource": null,
        "duplicateSource": null,
        "coreVersion": "12.331",
        "systemId": "dc20rpg",
        "systemVersion": "0.9.0",
        "createdTime": null,
        "modifiedTime": null,
        "lastModifiedBy": null
      },
      "_key": "!journal.pages!9pm4ha84o5zVTRth.66f68e2a863375af"
    },
    {
      "_id": "9df2e95138bc84a4",
      "name": "Defenses",
      "ownership": {
        "default": -1
      },
      "sort": 9,
      "text": {
        "content": "<p id=\"1cf1b90a-e081-818c-bbe4-fc3b73708cce\">When a creature makes an Attack (see the Combat Actions section) to attempt to deal damage to a target, the creature’s Check is compared against the value of one of the target’s Defenses (Active Defense or Passive Defense) to determine if the Attack hits.</p><p id=\"1cf1b90a-e081-81c9-bbf3-cda195ed403e\" class=\"block-color-purple_background\">DC Tip: Below are the 2 different types of Defense and which damage types usually target them. There can be unique instances where a damage type targets a different defense than usual, but each ability will always say which type of Defense it targets.</p>",
        "format": 1
      },
      "title": {
        "level": 1,
        "show": true
      },
      "type": "text",
      "system": {},
      "image": {},
      "video": {
        "controls": true,
        "volume": 0.5
      },
      "src": null,
      "flags": {},
      "_stats": {
        "compendiumSource": null,
        "duplicateSource": null,
        "coreVersion": "12.331",
        "systemId": "dc20rpg",
        "systemVersion": "0.9.0",
        "createdTime": null,
        "modifiedTime": 1744723066745,
        "lastModifiedBy": "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y"
      },
      "_key": "!journal.pages!9pm4ha84o5zVTRth.9df2e95138bc84a4"
    },
    {
      "_id": "ffe9b7f8e12c99fa",
      "name": "Precision Defense",
      "ownership": {
        "default": -1
      },
      "sort": 10,
      "text": {
        "content": "<p>Precision Defense (PD) measures a creature’s ability to avoid attacks that can be dodged, such as a precise strike or a ranged projectile. It reflects a combination of reflexes, and tactical foresight, making it a crucial defense against single-target assaults.</p>",
        "format": 1
      },
      "title": {
        "level": 2,
        "show": true
      },
      "type": "text",
      "system": {},
      "image": {},
      "video": {
        "controls": true,
        "volume": 0.5
      },
      "src": null,
      "flags": {},
      "_stats": {
        "compendiumSource": null,
        "duplicateSource": null,
        "coreVersion": "12.331",
        "systemId": "dc20rpg",
        "systemVersion": "0.9.0",
        "createdTime": null,
        "modifiedTime": 1744723128407,
        "lastModifiedBy": "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y"
      },
      "_key": "!journal.pages!9pm4ha84o5zVTRth.ffe9b7f8e12c99fa"
    },
    {
      "_id": "c96eafd77d0616ef",
      "name": "PD Calculation",
      "ownership": {
        "default": -1
      },
      "sort": 11,
      "text": {
        "content": "<p id=\"1cf1b90a-e081-8153-86a7-cbf4b09f4fe5\">Your PD is equal to 8 plus your Combat Mastery, Agility, and Intelligence. If you are wearing Armor or wielding a Shield (see <strong>Equipment</strong>), you also add their respective bonuses to your PD.</p><ul><li><p><strong>Agility:</strong> Represents your reaction speed and physical swiftness, allowing you to evade incoming attacks.</p></li><li><p><strong>Intelligence:</strong> Reflects your ability to anticipate danger and position yourself wisely, giving you the time needed to react.</p></li></ul><p id=\"1cf1b90a-e081-81b2-bf81-c04e53897686\"></p><p id=\"1cf1b90a-e081-81b2-bf81-c04e53897686\"><span style=\"border-bottom:0.05em solid\"><strong>PD Formula</strong></span></p><p id=\"1cf1b90a-e081-8177-a77b-e0228ee41577\" style=\"text-align:center\">8 + Combat Mastery + Agility + Intelligence + Armor &amp; Shield Bonuses</p>",
        "format": 1
      },
      "title": {
        "level": 3,
        "show": true
      },
      "type": "text",
      "system": {},
      "image": {},
      "video": {
        "controls": true,
        "volume": 0.5
      },
      "src": null,
      "flags": {},
      "_stats": {
        "compendiumSource": null,
        "duplicateSource": null,
        "coreVersion": "12.331",
        "systemId": "dc20rpg",
        "systemVersion": "0.9.0",
        "createdTime": null,
        "modifiedTime": 1744723354636,
        "lastModifiedBy": "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y"
      },
      "_key": "!journal.pages!9pm4ha84o5zVTRth.c96eafd77d0616ef"
    },
    {
      "_id": "de60a69ea06074a0",
      "name": "Area Defense",
      "ownership": {
        "default": -1
      },
      "sort": 13,
      "text": {
        "content": "<p>Area Defense (AD) measures a creature’s ability to withstand attacks that cannot be avoided, such as explosions, shockwaves, or other widespread effects. Instead of relying on dodging, Fortitude reflects raw endurance, resilience, and sheer force of will to endure the assault.</p>",
        "format": 1
      },
      "title": {
        "level": 2,
        "show": true
      },
      "type": "text",
      "system": {},
      "image": {},
      "video": {
        "controls": true,
        "volume": 0.5
      },
      "src": null,
      "flags": {},
      "_stats": {
        "compendiumSource": null,
        "duplicateSource": null,
        "coreVersion": "12.331",
        "systemId": "dc20rpg",
        "systemVersion": "0.9.0",
        "createdTime": null,
        "modifiedTime": 1744723213698,
        "lastModifiedBy": "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y"
      },
      "_key": "!journal.pages!9pm4ha84o5zVTRth.de60a69ea06074a0"
    },
    {
      "_id": "cbb28ae1423b478c",
      "name": "AD Calculation",
      "ownership": {
        "default": -1
      },
      "sort": 14,
      "text": {
        "content": "<p id=\"1cf1b90a-e081-8153-86a7-cbf4b09f4fe5\">Your AD is equal to 8 plus your Combat Mastery, Might, and Charisma. If you are wearing Armor or wielding a Shield (see <strong>Equipment</strong>), you also add their respective bonuses to your AD.</p><ul><li><p><strong>Might:</strong> Represents your physical toughness and endurance, allowing you to absorb and resist bodily harm.</p></li><li><p><strong>Charisma: </strong>Reflects your inner resolve and commanding presence, reinforcing your ability to withstand mental and supernatural assaults.</p></li></ul><p id=\"1cf1b90a-e081-81b2-bf81-c04e53897686\"></p><p id=\"1cf1b90a-e081-81b2-bf81-c04e53897686\"><span style=\"border-bottom:0.05em solid\"><strong>AD Formula</strong></span></p><p id=\"1cf1b90a-e081-8177-a77b-e0228ee41577\" style=\"text-align:center\">8 + Combat Mastery + Might + Charisma + Armor &amp; Shield Bonuses</p>",
        "format": 1
      },
      "title": {
        "level": 3,
        "show": true
      },
      "type": "text",
